<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,994,1018]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[325,473,994,1018]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Formallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipenis">
<emphasis box="[325,473,994,1018]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">F. longipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.A.Viraktamath" authorityYear="2011" box="[604,730,995,1018]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Formallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata">
<emphasis box="[604,730,995,1018]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">F. truncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it can be distinguished by the coarsely punctate almost immaculate pronotum, long aedeagal preatrium and the structure of the caudal lobe of the pygofer.
